{"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Fractions"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"","type":"heading","text":""},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Fractions are represented as BFraction values consisting of a numerator BInt value and a denominator BInt value. The representation is normalized:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The numerator and denominator have no common factors except 1","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The denominator is always positive","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Zero is represented as 0\/1"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"anchor":"Creating-BFractions","type":"heading","level":3,"text":"Creating BFraction’s"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Fractions are created by","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifying the numerator and denominator explicitly f.ex. BFraction(17, 4)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifying the decimal value explictly f.ex. BFraction(4.25)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using a string representation f.ex. BFraction(“4.25”)! or equivalently BFraction(“425E-2”)!"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Specifying a continued fraction like BFraction([3, 4, 12, 4]) equivalent to 649 \/ 200","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Defining a fraction by giving its decimal value (like 4.25) might lead to surprises,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"because not all decimal values can be represented exactly as a floating point number."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For example, one might think that BFraction(0.1) would equal 1\/10,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"but in fact it equals 3602879701896397 \/ 36028797018963968 = 0.1000000000000000055511151231257827021181583404541015625","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Converting-BFractions","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Converting BFraction’s"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"BFraction values can be converted to String values, to decimal String values, to Double values and to Continued Fraction values."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["let x = BFraction(1000, 7)","","\/\/ To String","let s1 = x.asString() \/\/ s1 = \"1000 \/ 7\"","","\/\/ To decimal String","let s1 = x.asDecimalString(precision: 8, exponential: false) \/\/ s1 = \"142.85714\"","let s2 = x.asDecimalString(precision: 8, exponential: true) \/\/ s2 = \"1.4285714E+2\"","","\/\/ To Double","let d = x.asDouble() \/\/ d = 142.8571428571429","","\/\/ To Continued Fraction","let f = x.asContinuedFraction() \/\/ f = [BInt(142), BInt(1), BInt(6)]"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Operations","level":3,"anchor":"Operations"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The operations available to fractions are:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Arithmetic","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"addition"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"subtraction","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"multiplication","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"division","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"modulo an integer","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"exponentiation"}]}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Rounding to an integer","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"round - to nearest integer","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"truncate - towards 0"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"ceil - towards +infinity","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"floor - towards -infinity","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Comparison - the six standard operations == != < <= > >=","type":"text"}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Bernoulli-Numbers","text":"Bernoulli Numbers","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The static function","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let bn = BFraction.bernoulli(n)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"computes the n’th (n >= 0) Bernoulli number, which is a rational number.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["print(BFraction.bernoulli(60))","print(BFraction.bernoulli(60).asDecimalString(precision: 20, exponential: true))"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"would print"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["-1215233140483755572040304994079820246041491 \/ 56786730","-2.1399949257225333665E+34"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}]},{"code":["let x = BFraction.bernoulliSequence(n)"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"computes the n even numbered Bernoulli numbers B(0), B(2) … B(2 * n - 2)."}]},{"text":"Harmonic Numbers","anchor":"Harmonic-Numbers","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The static function"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let Hn = BFraction.harmonic(n)"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"computes the n’th harmonic number, that is, 1 + 1\/2 + … + 1\/n","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The static function","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let x = BFraction.harmonicSequence(n)"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"returns an array containing the first n harmonic numbers.","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/bigint\/fractions"]}],"sections":[],"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Usage","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Examples","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Performance","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Chinese","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Dependencies","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/References","doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Algorithms"],"generated":true}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"BigInt"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Fractions","role":"article"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt"]]},"references":{"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt":{"role":"collection","title":"BigInt","abstract":[],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt","url":"\/documentation\/bigint","type":"topic"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/Chinese":{"url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/chinese","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Chinese","type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"article","title":"Chinese Remainder Theorem"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/Performance":{"url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/performance","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/BigInt\/documentation\/BigInt\/Performance","type":"topic","abstract":[],"role":"article","title":"Performance"},"doc://BigInt/documentation/BigInt/Usage":{"url":"\/documentation\/bigint\/usage","k